This paper is about improving the data efficiency of end-to-end text-to-speech (TTS) models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves using unpaired speech corpora and pre-training the model, which relates to unsupervised and semi-supervised learning, and could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper proposes using word embeddings, which is a common technique in machine learning and could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
